    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.31"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">31</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        <lb/>
                    1030 FIFTH AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi> 28
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>February 6, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm, Route No. 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Pursuant to the instructions of the Board of Directors of The Academy of American Poets, Inc., I call your attention to vacancy now existing in the Membership of the Board of Chancellors, due to the expiration of the term on January 9, 1958 of Mr. Randall Jarrell. Mr. Jarrell has served since 1956, when he succeeded Mr. Robinson Jeffers.</p>
                
                <p>A nominating blank is enclosed. Please note that you have the right to nominate two persons for this vacancy. Kindly date and sign the nomination blank, and return to me at your earliest convenience. Nominations will be closed March 10, 1958.</p>
                
                <p>It will be helpful if you would indicate briefly the reasons which motivate your nominations.</p>
                
                <p>The present Board of Chancellors and the pertinent provisions of the Charter and By-Laws governing the election of Chancellors are enclosed herewith. Chancellors may be re-elected as often as desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Hugh Bullock
                    Secretary</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">Enclosures</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
